## Reference conventions

{% include 'reference-conventions.md' %}

## What to populate

- `sections` — per reference-conventions.md. Each section is
  a rule category or band of guidance.
- `files` — usually empty (rules live in SKILL.md). Append
  only when a rule body is too long for SKILL.md or has
  independent reuse value.
- `rationale` — rule scope, what to include vs exclude, how
  prescriptive the language is.

## Output construction

```bash
LOOM=~/.kiro/skills/home/loom/scripts/loom.sh
WD={{ run.workdir }}

$LOOM output init "$WD" --task design

$LOOM output add "$WD" --task design \
    --set frontmatter.name=demo \
    --set frontmatter.type=reference \
    --set 'frontmatter.description=...' \
    --set 'sections[].heading=Required Behaviour' \
    --set 'sections[-1].outline=...' \
    --set 'sections[].heading=Forbidden Without Proof' \
    --set 'sections[-1].outline=...' \
    --set rationale='Rule scope and prescriptiveness tradeoffs...'
```

Syntax: `[]` appends, `[-1]` targets the last appended entry,
`.` nests.
